cover new information about a culture; the heart, or one’s motivation and confidence in dealing with a culture; and the body, or the capability to adapt actions and behavior so that they are appropriate in a new culture. A manager with a high CQ can enter into new cultural settings—national, professional, organizational, regional—and immediately understand what is happening and why, confidently interact with people, and engage in the right actions. Filled with real-world examples and case studies, this book explains how to assess one’s own skills and improve one’s CQ.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Management.2bisacsh1 aAng, Soon, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aTan, Joo-Seng, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150361971540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503619715423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503619715/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles